# 6. Core Interaction System (MVP)

## Purpose

This defines the first complete interaction loop in byDebut:

Create → Evaluate → Rank → Fork → Compare

---

## What this enables

The platform is not only identifying which variation is popular,
but also WHY one narrative path is stronger than another.

---

## Core Components

### 1. Create Variation UI
- User proposes a variable change
- Defines:
  - What changed
  - Why it matters
  - Expected outcome

---

### 2. Comment / Interpretation Layer
- Structured reflections (not free-form noise)
- Linked to specific parts of the variation

---

### 3. Voting + Ranking System
- Multi-dimensional scoring:
  - Coherence
  - Stability
  - Originality
  - Emotional impact

- Produces:
  - Ranked variations
  - Signal of narrative strength

---

### 4. Fork from Ranked Variation
- Users can branch from any ranked version
- Keeps lineage (version tree)

---

### 5. Comparison View
- Side-by-side variations
- Highlights:
  - What changed
  - Why it matters
  - Impact on outcome

---

## System Insight

This is the first part of byDebut that starts to look useful for:

- Story validation
- Creative collaboration
- Film industry evaluation

---

## Next Step

Connect this flow to the Variation Generator so that:

When a user forks a ranked variation:
